## Cost Optimization Triggers

### When to Upgrade
- **Render**: Monitor memory usage. FastAPI at sustained >80% of 512MB → upgrade to Standard ($25/mo, 2GB)
- **Neon**: At 0.4GB storage → upgrade to Scale ($19/mo, 10GB)
- **Upstash**: At 400K commands/month → switch to Pay-as-you-go ($0.20/100K)
- **Cloud Vision**: At 1K pages/mo → starts costing $0.0015/page (still negligible)

### When to Re-evaluate Providers
- At 10K+ users: evaluate GCP Cloud Run vs Render (Cloud Run scales to zero off-season, could save $7/mo × 8 idle months = $56/yr)
- At 50K+ users: evaluate self-hosted PaddleOCR on dedicated instance to replace Cloud Vision API (saves per-request cost, but adds hosting cost)
- At 100K+ users: evaluate OpenAI batch API (50% discount) for non-real-time processing

### Cost Reduction Levers (in priority order)
1. **OpenAI batch API**: for insights generation (non-real-time), 50% discount
2. **GPT-4o-mini → GPT-4.1-mini**: watch for cheaper models with same structured output quality
3. **Preprocessing tuning**: improve Pillow preprocessing to reduce GPT-4o vision fallback from 10% to 5% (saves $0.001/user)
4. **Cloud Run migration**: for off-season (May-December) when traffic is minimal
5. **Self-host Redis**: if Upstash exceeds $10/mo, a tiny Redis instance on Render is $7/mo

